'''Project Zomboid Script Support''' is an extension for [[Visual Studio Code]] that provides syntax highlighting for [[scripts]].

== Installation ==
To use the Project Zomboid Scripts extension, simply search in the Visual Studio Code extension menu for [https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=cyberbobjr.pz-syntax-extension â€œProject Zomboid Script Support by cyberbobjr]. Install it and it should detect automatically the [[Scripts#Module block|module block]] of script files to enable itself. If it does not, you can manually set the language module by clicking on the language mode button in the bottom right corner of Visual Studio Code and selecting ''Project Zomboid Scripts''.

